## Monuments  

Sutherland’s controversial figure has been commemorated through several monuments:  

* A **monument on Ben Bhraggie** near [Golspie](/Golspie) (often referred to as “the Mannie”).  
* The **Lilleshall Monument** in [Shropshire](/Shropshire), a 70‑foot‑high obelisk erected in 1833.  
* A colossal statue in the **Trentham Gardens Estate**, [Trentham, Staffordshire](/Trentham,_Staffordshire), designed by Winks and sculptured by Sir [Francis Leggatt Chantrey](/Francis_Leggatt_Chantrey).  

These monuments have sparked debate over time. In 1994, a proposal to demolish the “Mannie” was floated, later revised to relocate it to the grounds of [Dunrobin Castle](/Dunrobin_Castle). A failed attempt to topple the statue occurred in November 2011, but as of September 2024 it still stands, viewed by many as an essential historical reminder.  

